    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Connarus smeathmannii are respiratory issues such as bronchitis, with its expectorant properties helping to loosen and clear mucus from the lungs. Connarus smeathmannii has been traditionally used to treat gastrointestinal disorders like diarrhea, by virtue of its anthraquinone content which has purgative and anti-inflammatory effects. Its antiseptic and antimicrobial properties have been used to treat skin conditions such as eczema, by reducing inflammation and preventing bacterial infections. Additionally, Connarus smeathmannii has been found to be effective in reducing fever, due to its pyrogenic and anti-pyretic properties. Furthermore, the plant has been used to treat urinary tract infections, with its antibacterial activity helping to combat bacterial growth in the urinary system.",
