    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Connarus smeathmannii are its anti-inflammatory activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, such as quercetin and kaempferol, that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The plant's antioxidant properties, responsible for its ability to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress, are due to the presence of saponins, including glycosides and triterpenes. Connarus smeathmannii also exhibits antimicrobial activity, effective against a range of microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, thanks to the presence of volatile oils, such as borneol and bornyl acetate. Additionally, the plant's antiparasitic properties, which have been used to treat various parasitic infections, are attributed to the presence of alkaloids, including isoquinoline and benzylisoquinoline derivatives. The plant's ability to modulate the immune system and exhibit immunomodulatory activity is also a notable therapeutic property, which is attributed to the presence of various bioactive compounds, including polysaccharides and phenolic acids.",
