    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Connarus smeathmannii are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and alkaloids, which contribute to its medicinal properties. Flavonoids present in Connarus smeathmannii include kaempferol, quercetin, and isorhapontigenin, which exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities. Phenolic acids such as ferulic acid and sinapic acid in Connarus smeathmannii possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which may help in wound healing and tissue protection. Alkaloids like connaridine and connanidine in Connarus smeathmannii have shown antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activities, which may aid in the treatment of infections and inflammatory diseases. These constituents have been isolated and characterized through various chemical and biological assays, providing evidence for their potential healing properties.",
