    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Connarus smeathmannii improperly are experience nausea, develop allergic reactions, cause diarrhea, induce nausea, and suffer from diarrhea. These side effects can occur due to the plant's toxic compounds, such as saponins and flavonoids, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation and allergic responses. Prolonged consumption of the plant can also lead to gastrointestinal disturbances, including diarrhea and nausea, as the body tries to eliminate the toxic compounds. In severe cases, allergic reactions can manifest as skin rashes, itching, and respiratory issues, which can be life-threatening if not treated promptly. It is essential to consult a medical professional before using Connarus smeathmannii to ensure safe and proper usage.",
